      "message": "i\u0027m a bit lost here.  the BPF registers are all 32-bits right ?  on a system with 64-bit syscall args, we\u0027re writing 32-bit BPF insns to test those values ?  so how can we omit the test ?\n\nsay the filter has:\n\n close: arg0 \u003c 0x10\n\narg0 is a 64-bit register.  if you omit the hi\u003d\u003d0 part, won\u0027t someone be able to call close(0xff00000000) ?  hi\u003d0xff and lo\u003d0x00000000.",
