      "writtenOn": "2018-07-23T17:53:35Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "That would be implemented as\n\n close: !(arg0 \u003e\u003d 0x10)\n\nso that would roughly translate to\n\n if (hi(arg0) \u003e hi(0x10)) jump KILL;\n if (hi(arg0) \u003d\u003d hi(0x10) \u0026\u0026 lo(arg0) \u003e\u003d lo(0x10)) jump KILL;\n jump ALLOW;\n\nWhat this optimization does is that it removes the first part of the second if, (|hi(arg0) \u003d\u003d hi(0x10)|), given that we know it\u0027s going to be true always, since |!(hi(arg0) \u003e hi(0x10))|, which means that the only value |hi(arg0)| can legally have is zero. We\u0027d still be doing the very first check, so any non-zero |hi(arg0)| value should still jump to KILL.\n\nLet me see if I can reword this to be clearer.",
